<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 12:57:04 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>近年来，美国人对中国的看法变得更加积极</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</link><description>大多数美国人仍然对中国持负面看法，但最近的一项调查显示，对中国的好感度有所上升，尤其是在民主党人和年轻人中。现在称中国为敌人的人越来越少了。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</guid></item><item><title>当地新闻情况说明书</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/fact-sheet/local-news-fact-sheet/</link><description>自 2016 年以来，美国人对当地新闻的关注度有所下降。探索当今人们如何获取当地新闻，从电视和印刷媒体转向数字来源。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:04:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/fact-sheet/local-news-fact-sheet/</guid></item><item><title>美国大多数新数据中心都将落户农村地区</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/13/most-new-data-centers-in-the-us-are-coming-to-rural-areas/</link><description>全国正在建设超过 1,500 个新数据中心。大多数将建在农村地区，特别是南部和中西部，标志着从城市地点的转变。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 01:22:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/13/most-new-data-centers-in-the-us-are-coming-to-rural-areas/</guid></item><item><title>美国人仍然选择纸质书籍而不是数字或音频版本；很少有人参加读书俱乐部</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/09/americans-still-opt-for-print-books-over-digital-or-audio-versions-few-are-in-book-clubs/</link><description>大多数美国成年人都读书，尽管电子书和有声读物的使用有所增长，但纸质书仍然比数字格式更受青睐。习惯因人群而异，很少有人参加读书俱乐部。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 01:18:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/09/americans-still-opt-for-print-books-over-digital-or-audio-versions-few-are-in-book-clubs/</guid></item><item><title>最高法院多久推翻自己的判决？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/08/how-often-does-the-supreme-court-overturn-its-own-decisions/</link><description>只有不到 1% 的最高法院案件推翻了旧的判决。其中一半以上案件涉及经济活动或刑事诉讼。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 01:07:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/08/how-often-does-the-supreme-court-overturn-its-own-decisions/</guid></item><item><title>视频：民意调查能告诉我们谁会在选举日获胜吗？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/04/08/video-can-polls-tell-us-who-will-win-on-election-day/</link><description>我们经常听到候选人领先、落后，或者比赛打平。这是基于“赛马”民意调查，该民意调查根据人们如何回答选举前的调查来估计候选人的支持率。但由于某些原因，准确测量赛马情况非常困难。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:52:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/04/08/video-can-polls-tell-us-who-will-win-on-election-day/</guid></item><item><title>美国人尤其是年轻人对以色列和内塔尼亚胡的负面看法持续上升</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/negative-views-of-israel-netanyahu-continue-to-rise-among-americans-especially-young-people/</link><description>美国成年人对以色列和本杰明·内塔尼亚胡的看法变得更加负面，两党中 50 岁以下的大多数人对他们的评价都很差。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 01:17:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/negative-views-of-israel-netanyahu-continue-to-rise-among-americans-especially-young-people/</guid></item><item><title>汽油价格是伊朗战争中美国人最关心的问题</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/07/gas-prices-are-americans-top-concern-in-iran-war/</link><description>69%的美国人担心伊朗战争导致天然气价格上涨，45%的人表示美国在避免平民伤亡方面做得不够。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 01:02:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/07/gas-prices-are-americans-top-concern-in-iran-war/</guid></item><item><title>美国人从哪里获取健康信息以及他们信任什么？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/07/where-do-americans-get-health-information-and-what-do-they-trust/</link><description>医疗保健提供者是健康信息的重要来源。较小的份额从社交媒体和人工智能获取健康信息。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:47:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/04/07/where-do-americans-get-health-information-and-what-do-they-trust/</guid></item><item><title>大约一半有兄弟姐妹的美国人至少与其中一个人关系密切</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/about-half-of-americans-with-siblings-are-close-to-at-least-one-of-them/</link><description>大约一半有兄弟姐妹的美国成年人与至少一个人非常或极其亲密，但亲密程度和支持程度因人口统计数据而异。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:32:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/07/about-half-of-americans-with-siblings-are-close-to-at-least-one-of-them/</guid></item></channel></rss>